-- Egypt Stock Movers: Al Baraka Bank, Citadel Capital Are Active
-- B y   A h m e d   A .   N a m a t a l l a
-- 2012-03-11T13:17:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-11/egypt-stock-movers-al-baraka-bank-citadel-capital-are-active.html
Egypt ’s benchmark  EGX30 Index (EGX30) 
retreated for a second day, losing 1.8 percent to 5,300.26 at
the 2:30 p.m. close in Cairo for the biggest drop in almost
three weeks.  The following shares were active on the Egyptian Exchange.
Stock symbols follow company names.  Al Baraka Bank Egypt ESC (SAUD)   declined 2.3 percent to
10.76 Egyptian pounds, the lowest level in almost a week. The
Cairo-based unit of  Albaraka Banking Group (BARKA)  said 2011 profit
declined 7.7 percent to 100.1 million pounds ($16.6 million)
compared with a year earlier.  Citadel Capital SAE (CCAP)  (CCAP EY) fell 2.7 percent to 3.58
pounds, the lowest level in more than two weeks. The private
equity firm said its Golden Crescent Investments Ltd. unit will
receive 437.5 million common shares and another $60 million in
preferred shares in  Sea Dragon Energy Inc. (SDX)  as payment for a
stake in National Petroleum Co. Egypt Ltd.  An earlier deal granted Golden Crescent common shares and
$60 million in cash. Citadel said the revised agreement doesn’t
change the $147.5 million value of the transaction.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ahmed A Namatalla in Cairo at 
 anamatalla@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
